<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALTON OBVIOUSLY HAS A LOT TO LEARN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jerome Walton's comments about teachers were those of an ignorant and foolish 
man. The fact that The Times chose to print them reflects not only a certain 
insensitivity on the part of your editors, but also the perception that 
teachers are underpaid because their jobs are easy and unimportant. 
</P>
<P>
The lopsided values of society can never be changed while so-called leading 
publications give any sort of credence to the comments of those whose only 
virtues lie in their physical skills. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM WAXMAN, Ocean View High School, Huntington Beach 
</P>
