<HEADLINE>
<P>
WALTON OBVIOUSLY HAS A LOT TO LEARN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How can Jerome Walton (Morning Briefing, May 13) compare a professional sport 
to teaching? Teaching involves management and appropriate response to more 
stimuli per minute than most other professions. 
</P>
<P>
Baseball players have some time to rest on the bench, but teachers, even at 
their break times, are making phone calls to parents or preparing for their 
class. 
</P>
<P>
The staff of Children's Choice/McDowell Elementary Campus in Laguna Niguel 
invite Mr. Walton to come and experience a day with teachers and students. 
</P>
<P>
With a lot of rest the night before, he may survive. 
</P>
<P>
SHEREE ANN SCHUMACKER, El Toro 
</P>
