THE 'SATURDAY NIGHT LIVE' CAST PROTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is time to take a stand against the eroding of values, and the entertainment 
industry is perhaps the worst offender. Clay has a right to say what he feels, 
but I disagree with TV executives who allow him to reach a mammoth audience. 
</P>
<P>
Why is this country so eager to make itself look, in the eyes of the world, 
like bunch of foul-mouthed morons? Don't our politicians make us look bad 
enough? 
</P>
<P>
