<HEADLINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH TO MARK JULY 4 ON THE 3RD TO SAVE MONEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city is moving its Fourth of July celebrations to July 3 because of higher 
overtime rates in a new contract with police officers. The switch will save 
about $16,000 in police salaries and $4,000 in pay to other city workers, the 
city's chief administrative officer said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
