<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : CAMP PENDLETON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Marine Corps has placed mandatory restrictions on water use at Camp 
Pendleton and will issue warnings or citations to water wasters. 
</P>
<P>
Residents of the base, which receives water from its own underground wells, can 
water their lawns for only 30 minutes twice a week, between the hours of 6 p.m. 
and 7 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in about 20 years that water conservation measures will 
be enforced rather than voluntary at the base. 
</P>
<P>
Camp Pendleton joins 18 cities and water agencies in San Diego County that have 
agreed to mandatory water savings. 
</P>
