<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WEIL PITCHES NO-HITTER TO LEAD HART TO 7-1 WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Senior right-hander Kym Weil lost her perfect game and shutout in the seventh 
inning but still threw a no-hitter to lead Hart High to a 7-1 win over Rio Mesa 
Friday in a first-round Southern Section 4-A Division softball playoff game at 
Hart. 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa (13-10) scored in the seventh when a runner reached base on a fielding 
error and scored on a throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
Weil (25-2) struck out 12 and walked none. 
</P>
<P>
Heather Medearis and Stephanie Keeler each had two hits for Hart (26-3), the 
top-seeded team in the division. Hart will play Torrance, a 3-0 winner over 
Long Beach Poly on Friday, on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
In other 4-A games: 
</P>
<P>
Crescenta Valley 2, Burroughs 1 -- Both Crescenta Valley runs scored on errors 
in the second inning at Montrose Field. 
</P>
<P>
Becki Mixon (24-2), a sophomore, struck out eight and scattered five hits for 
the Falcons. 
</P>
<P>
Buena 4, Hoover 0 -- Freshman Nancy Evans struck out 10 and allowed six hits, 
but Hoover (17-6) stranded 10 runners and fell in the first round to host Buena 
(19-6). 
</P>
<P>
1-A DIVISION 
</P>
<P>
Paraclete 11, Oak Park 0 -- Laura Staats held Oak Park (16-8) to three hits and 
struck out 13. Kelli Rommey had two Oak Park hits. 
</P>
<P>
La Reina 9, San Gabriel Mission 3 -- Sheri Sisco struck out 17, and Valerie 
Serpico hit a home run, the first time a ball has cleared the fence at La Reina 
in more than five years. 
</P>
<P>
Serpico's two-run home run cleared a fence 190 feet away in right-center field. 
Sisco (7-2), a senior right-hander, struck out eight in a row at one point for 
La Reina (21-5). 
</P>
<P>
Santa Paula 12, Village Christian 0 -- Santa Paula senior left-hander Julie 
Coert (4-4) struck out six, allowed only three hits, walked none and helped her 
own cause with a run-scoring double. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Paula (13-13) will play La Reina in a second-round game Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 11, L.A. Baptist 0 -- Junior right-hander Melissa Thatcher (20-5) threw 
a one-hitter and hit a two-run double against visiting L. A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
Jill Hartwig was two for four with a three-run triple for Agoura (21-5). 
</P>
<P>
SMALL SCHOOLS DIVISION 
</P>
<P>
Crossroads 19, Highland Hall 11 -- Crossroads' Melony Berkey was three for four 
with two doubles and two RBIs against visiting Highland Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Stephanie Reisberg had three hits, and Rebecca Bloom (11-5) earned the win for 
Crossroads (12-6). 
</P>
<P>
Ribet Academy 7, Oakwood 3 -- Ribet Academy's Kate Stoll, a converted catcher, 
pitched a no-hitter but walked 14 at Ribet Academy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
