<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A measure that would allow Illinois universities to pay student-athletes and 
would regulate athletic associations' investigations of college sports programs 
passed its first hurdle in the Illinois House of Representatives. 
</P>
<P>
Under the bill, universities could decide to pay student athletes a stipend of 
up to $250 a month. 
</P>
<P>
The measure was sent to the Illinois Senate on a 71-37 vote. However, it would 
not apply to the current NCAA investigation of the University of Illinois 
basketball program and would only take effect if five other nearby states 
enacted similar laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
