<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge junior Bob Burns shot a final-round 75 to earn medalist 
honors in the NCAA Division II golf championships at Jupiter, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
He finished with a 288, the only player to match par over four rounds on the 
6,850-yard course. Florida Southern won the team title with 1,170, 26 strokes 
ahead of Columbus College of Georgia. Northridge was third with 1,198. 
</P>
