<P>
SANDBERG ERRS AFTER 123 GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ryne Sandberg's record streak of 123 games without an error ended Friday night 
with a wild throw against the Houston Astros. 
</P>
<P>
Sandberg, the Chicago Cubs' Gold Glove second baseman, fielded a deflected 
ground ball by Eric Anthony in the fourth inning but threw wide of first 
baseman Mark Grace. 
</P>
<P>
Sandberg successfully handled 582 consecutive chances without an error. His 
last error had come June 20 against the Pittsburgh Pirates. Sandberg's streak 
set a major league record for infielders, excluding first basemen. 
</P>
