<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
4 YOUTHS NAMED TO MILITARY ACADEMIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROLYN KUSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four Ventura County youths have been appointed to U.S. military academies. 
</P>
<P>
Justin Peddicord, a senior at Nordhoff High School in Ojai; Zachary Zeiner, a 
student at New Mexico Military Institute; and Brian Kobashigawa, a 1989 
graduate of Channel Islands High School, will attend the U.S. Air Force Academy 
in Colorado Springs this fall. 
</P>
<P>
Ted Lawrence, a senior at Santa Clara High School, will attend the U.S. 
Military Academy at West Point. 
</P>
<P>
Rep. Robert J. Lagomarsino (R-Ventura), who made the appointments, praised the 
youths for maintaining high grade averages in school and participating in 
extracurricular activities. "Their parents and the community can take pride in 
their appointment," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Peddicord of Ojai is a varsity tennis and soccer player. Zeiner, also of Ojai, 
was captain of the varsity soccer team and played varsity football at Nordhoff 
High School. Kobashigawa of Oxnard was a member of his school's academic 
decathlon team and has received an academic achievement award in science. 
Lawrence of Oxnard was captain of the varsity football team. CAROLYN KUSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
