<HEADLINE>
<P>
HINES LEADS SADDLEBACK TO STATE TITLE IN TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carl Hines won in singles and doubles play and Saddleback College defeated West 
Valley, 5-4, to win its third consecutive state tennis championship Friday at 
Westmont College. 
</P>
<P>
Hines, the Gauchos' No. 1 player, defeated Juan Lavalle, 7-6, 6-1, 6-4. Hines 
then teamed with Stan Sanders to defeat Lavalle and Mark Edmunds, 6-3, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
"Carl has been our bread and butter all season," Saddleback Coach Bill Otta 
said. "We needed him to be strong today and he was." 
</P>
<P>
The state title was the fourth in seven years for Saddleback (24-0). 
</P>
</TEXT>
